# Line-ending policy — determinism first (doc 02 §Determinism, doc 05/10).
#
# The engine and its checked-in generated artifacts (roff man pages) are
# compared byte-for-byte across Linux/macOS/Windows in CI. Without this, git on
# Windows checks the LF-committed files out as CRLF, and byte-exact tests such as
# the man-page staleness guard fail on the trailing \r. Force LF in the working
# tree on every platform so what CI reads matches what the generator produces.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Man pages are text and must stay LF regardless of extension heuristics.
*.1 text eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending normalized (future golden fixtures).
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.webp binary
*.bmp binary
*.woff binary
*.woff2 binary
